  "prompt": "How much are 4 tons of gold worth?",
  "response": "The value of gold fluctuates based on market conditions. As of October 2023, the price of gold is approximately $1,800 per ounce. There are 32,000 ounces in a ton, so for 4 tons of gold, the calculation would be as follows:\n\n\\[ 4 \\text{ tons} \\times 32,000 \\text{ ounces/ton} = 128,000 \\text{ ounces} \\]\n\n\\[ 128,000 \\text{ ounces} \\times \\$1,800/\\text{ounce} = \\$230,400,000 \\]\n\nTherefore, 4 tons of gold would be worth approximately \\$230,400,000. This value could change depending on the current market price of gold.",
